# Local denylist for the pre-commit sanitization hook.
#
# Copy this file to .githooks/local-denylist and customize. The actual
# .githooks/local-denylist is gitignored — your personal patterns never
# enter the repo.
#
# Format (one pattern per line): <description>|<extended-regex>
#
# - Lines starting with # are comments.
# - Blank lines are ignored.
# - Patterns are matched against `+` lines in `git diff --cached`.
# - Use \b for word boundaries to avoid false-positives on substrings.
#
# Examples (replace with your own):
#
# Personal email|alex@example\.com
# Personal domain|example\.com
# My last name|\bSmith\b
# My full name|Alex Smith
# Institution|\b(University of Example|UoE)\b
# Collaborator surnames|\b(Jones|Lee|Patel)\b
# Project-specific keywords|\b(internal-codename|secret-feature)\b
# Old project ID we rotated|abc123xyz789
